 <text>
  <front>
   <head>TO ANNA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">faded lip may oft to thee</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">As gay a smile, my Anna, wear,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">As when in youth, from sorrow free,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I only shed the transient tear.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And oft chill Autumn's varying day,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Resembles April's genial hours;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And glitters with the noontide ray,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Though oftener dark with clouds and showers.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, when I join the social throng,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This heart as warmly seems to glow</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">As when my pensive early song</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Was only tuned to fancied woe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And oft we see gay ivy's wreath</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The tree with brilliant bloom o'erspread,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When, part its leaves, and gaze beneath,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We find the hidden tree is dead.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
